# Gen-Z Life Simulator

A text-based life simulation game built in Java where a university
student attempts to survive a 7-day week balancing study, work,
and social life.

## Features
- 7-day simulation with 9 activity types across 4 categories
- Probabilistic events with random outcomes per activity
- 4 early termination conditions (burnout, exhaustion, etc.)
- Gen-Z Survival Score (GZSS) with 5 possible endings

## Tech Stack
- Java
- OOP principles: inheritance, polymorphism, abstract classes, enums

## How to Run
1. Clone the repo
2. Compile: `javac GenZLifeSimulator.java`
3. Run: `java GenZLifeSimulator`

## Course
